#!/usr/local/projects/routing/help/html_filter.pl
<h2 align=center>Help for the "Donation maximum" for the "Staff" table</h2>

"Donation maximum" and "Donation percentage" work together to determine
what level of payment the driver is requesting in monthly expense reports.

When generating automatic expense reports for volunteers, drivers can
donate from 0 to 100% of their reimbursable mileage, up to a maximum
set here in dollars.  By default, the donation percentage and maximum
are both set to zero which means that software will use the full amount
of the expense report for payment.  If the donation percentage is 100%
and the donation maximum is set to a really big number, the software
will assume that the expense report will be zero.

